result.execSummary:
The defendant Seda M Sarlioglu was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Seda M Sarlioglu in court, in custody, with attorney Amber K. Rumpf.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.Defendant enters a guilty plea to count #1. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #1. Counts #2-4, and case #16CF1576 are dismissed and read in. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Rumpf makes statements regarding sentencing. Defendant makes Statements. The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT#1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   	***CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE, CONCURRENT TO 15CF740*** 

__4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 60 days)
  -  2 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISON 

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS			***TRANSFER ALLOWED TO MILWAUKEE COUNTY***	***CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE, CONCURRENT TO 15CF740*** 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 			

____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol, illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
Prescribed;
____Inform Agent of all prescriptions, sign releases;
____Obtain all prescriptions through one source;
____Inform any treating medical personnel of case
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain/work toward employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with:any co-actor, victim, or witness listed in the criminal complaint
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 
____Mental Heath / Psychological Evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate

RESTITUTION:  $1000.00 to Associated Bank, $800.00 to Tri-City Bank (Joint and Several, to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)

COSTS:  $278.00 + $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation) 

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
